  Rootkit: {
    rank: 2,
    type: "Electronic Warfare",
    approach: null,
    skill: "Computers",
    flavor: "A rootkit is a piece of software designed to hide itself and its payload from detection. Installing a rootkit on a node allows you to operate on that node without being physically present, making it an invaluable tool for any operator who wants to maintain a foothold in a network without risking exposure.",
    description: """
      <h3>Activation:</h3>
      <p>As a Scheme action, make a <strong>Computers check</strong> at the network's TN, targeting one node where you hold a foothold.</p>
      <h3>Effects:</h3>
      <p>If you succeed, you install a rootkit on the target node, allowing you to target objects on the network with techniques that require a foothold on the node regardless of your actual position. The rootkit remains active for a number of rounds equal to your bonus successes (minimum 1). You can only have one rootkit active at a time; installing a new one overwrites the previous one.</p>
    """
  },
  "Dead Drop": {
    rank: 1,
    type: "Electronic Warfare",
    approach: "Resilience",
    skill: "Computers",
    flavor: "Tradecraft did not die with the digital age. It adapted. A hidden cache buried in a node's architecture serves the same purpose as a chalk mark on a mailbox: someone left something, and only the right people know where to look.",
    description: """
      <h3>Activation:</h3>
      <p>As a Scheme action, make a <strong>Computers [Resilience] check</strong> at the network's TN.</p>
