  Spoof: {
    rank: 2,
    type: "Electronic Warfare",
    approach: null,
    skill: "Computers",
    flavor: "Sensors trust their own data. That is their greatest vulnerability. A spoofed feed shows an empty hallway while a team walks through it. A motion sensor registers nothing. A biometric reader accepts a face that was never scanned. The system works perfectly. It is simply wrong.",
    description: """
      <h3>Activation:</h3>
      <p>As a Scheme action, make a <strong>Computers check</strong> at the network's TN, targeting one sensor, camera, or input device on a node where you hold a foothold.</p>
      <h3>Effects:</h3>
      <p>If you succeed, the device reports whatever you want it to report for a number of rounds equal to 1 plus your bonus successes. The spoof is convincing enough to pass casual inspection, but an operator who knows what to look for can detect it with a successful <strong>TN 2 Computers check</strong>.</p>
      <h3>New Opportunities:</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>(op)+:</strong> Increase the difficulty of detecting the spoof by 1 per (op) spent this way.</li>
        <li><strong>(op)+:</strong> The spoof persists for one additional round per (op) spent this way.</li>
      </ul>
    """
  },
  "Falsify Data": {
    rank: 2,
    type: "Electronic Warfare",
    approach: null,
    skill: "Computers",
    flavor: "Forgery is a crime as old as writing itself. In the digital age, it is not just signatures on paper that can be faked. A forged file can be indistinguishable from the original, and a forged record can rewrite history. The ability to create convincing fakes is a powerful tool for any operator.",
    description: """
      <h3>Activation:</h3>
      <p>As a Scheme action, make a <strong>Computers check</strong> at the network's TN, targeting one file or record on a node where you hold a foothold.</p>
      <h3>Effects:</h3>
      <p>If you succeed, you replace the target file or record with a forgery of your design. The forgery is convincing enough to pass casual inspection, but an operator who knows what to look for can detect it with a successful <strong>TN 2 Computers check</strong>.</p>
      <h3>New Opportunities:</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>(op)+:</strong> Increase the difficulty of detecting the forgery by 1 per (op) spent this way.</li>
      </ul>
    """
