      <p>If you succeed, you take control of the device for as long as you maintain concentration. You may issue one command to the device as part of this action; subsequent commands require you to spend your action on your turn. The device continues its last order until commanded otherwise. If you take any other action, you must make a <strong>Computers check</strong> at the network's TN at the start of your next turn to maintain control, or the device reverts to its default behavior.</p>
    """
  },
  "Cleanup Detail": {
    rank: 2,
    type: "Electronic Warfare",
    approach: null,
    skill: "Computers",
    flavor: "",
    description: """
      <h3>Activation:</h3>
      <p>As a Scheme action, make a <strong>Computers check</strong> at the network's TN, targeting one node where you hold a foothold.</p>
      <h3>Effects:</h3>
      <p>If you succeed, you remove all previous traces of your presence on the target node, including any devices you have hijacked, any rootkits you have installed, and any data you have exfiltrated. This does not prevent an operator from detecting that the node was accessed, but it does prevent them from determining who accessed it or what they did.</p>
      <p>This does not affect actions taken after you use this technique or nodes you do not currently have a foothold on. If you return to the node later, you will need to use this technique again to remove traces of your new activity.</p>
