  "Total Eclipse": {
    rank: 3,
    type: "Electronic Warfare",
    approach: null,
    skill: "Computers",
    flavor: "There is a point past hacking where the distinction between operator and infrastructure dissolves. Administrative control is not a privilege the network grants. It is a condition the network cannot prevent. What follows is total authority, and then total collapse, because no system survives being owned that completely.",
    description: """
      <h3>Activation:</h3>
      <p>As a Scheme action, <strong>Immediately increase your heat by 5</strong> and make a <strong>Computers check</strong> at the network's TN +2. There is no heat cost associated with failing this technique.</p>
      <h3>Effects:</h3>
      <p>On success, you assume administrative control of the entire network for a number of rounds equal to your bonus successes (minimum 1). While in control, you may issue one command per round to any device on the network as a free action, sentries treat you as an authorized operator and obey your commands, and barriers open or close at your will. At the end of the duration, the network crashes and reboots: all connections are severed, all sentries reboot, and the network goes offline for the remainder of the scene. Your Heat immediately goes to 10 (Burned) when the duration ends, but the crash means there is no network left to trace you on; the physical security response, if any, depends on how fast they can figure out what happened.</p>
    """
  },
  "Closing Strike": {
    rank: 2,
    type: "Combat",
    approach: null,
    skill: "Blades",
    flavor: "Many would mistake distance from a blade user for safety, but a true master of the sword can cover ground in the blink of an eye, crossing surprising gaps.",
    description: """
